Dialogue: 0,0:14:20.14,0:14:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Ineffable means it is not within the linear.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:22.50,0:14:23.50,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not definable.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:23.50,0:14:27.24,Default,,0,0,0,,It is not describable.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:27.24,0:14:28.77,Default,,0,0,0,,You cannot circumscribe it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:28.77,0:14:31.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You can't catch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:31.50,0:14:32.47,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the way you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:32.47,0:14:40.91,Default,,0,0,0,,So, by intention then, your life becomes, becomes that intention.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:40.91,0:14:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You become it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:42.76,0:14:44.16,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the prayer.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:44.16,0:14:51.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of praying from a me to a that, you become that.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:51.25,0:14:53.48,Default,,0,0,0,,You are it.
Dialogue: 0,0:14:53.48,0:15:02.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, as you walk through the woods, do you know that the plants know that?
Dialogue: 0,0:15:02.01,0:15:05.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The first time I went to that state, I walked through the woods.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:05.01,0:15:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All of life was like worshipful, worshipful of the presence of divinity and was very conscious
Dialogue: 0,0:15:13.50,0:15:15.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and aware of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:15.36,0:15:16.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Very conscious of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:16.36,0:15:21.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And I was also conscious and aware of the divinity of everything else that exists.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:21.50,0:15:24.45,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, universe is conscious.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:24.45,0:15:26.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It is conscious and aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:26.94,0:15:31.17,Default,,0,0,0,,The tree does know, does actually know what you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:31.17,0:15:37.12,Default,,0,0,0,,Let's see if that's so.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:37.12,0:15:38.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a fact, the Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:38.17,0:15:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Resist.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:39.53,0:15:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a fact.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:40.53,0:15:46.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When I first saw it shimmering forth, I thought, this is like a psychedelic cartoon or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:46.53,0:15:57.74,Default,,0,0,0,,I expect to hear the old submarine in the background.
Dialogue: 0,0:15:57.74,0:16:03.13,Default,,0,0,0,,The tree is vibrantly aware that it is in the presence of divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:03.13,0:16:06.25,Default,,0,0,0,,It has no problem with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:06.25,0:16:13.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Because of its nature, because of its, because of the source of its creation, which is the
Dialogue: 0,0:16:13.32,0:16:18.13,Default,,0,0,0,,same source as your creation, it knows its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:18.13,0:16:24.08,Default,,0,0,0,,Life reverences life above 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:24.08,0:16:28.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Below 200 is a different story.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:28.61,0:16:31.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So that's enough for lunch.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:31.46,0:16:36.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm happy we weren't wrong about anything today.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:36.13,0:16:39.25,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate to have lightning interrupt a lecture.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:39.25,0:16:46.94,Default,,0,0,0,,You just made a boo-boo at a thousand.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:46.94,0:16:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,What time do we resume?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:47.94,0:16:48.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Two o'clock.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:48.94,0:16:50.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that still on?
Dialogue: 0,0:16:50.41,0:16:51.41,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,0:16:51.41,0:17:26.96,Default,,0,0,0,,So we've got plenty of time for lunch, and it's been a wonderful morning, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:26.96,0:17:34.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Everyone is here.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:34.25,0:17:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,We're going to get into the dualities that hold the levels of consciousness where they
Dialogue: 0,0:17:39.63,0:17:40.63,Default,,0,0,0,,are.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:40.63,0:17:41.63,Default,,0,0,0,,People are interested.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:41.63,0:17:46.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Now I see the pattern, you know, how do I transcend the stairway?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:46.93,0:17:51.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The stairway to God, that's what I call it, you know, calibrated levels of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:51.96,0:17:54.66,Default,,0,0,0,,How do you transcend the stairway?
Dialogue: 0,0:17:54.66,0:17:56.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,0:17:56.17,0:18:01.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The power of intention, of course, will align you with the correct way to go, because it
Dialogue: 0,0:18:01.88,0:18:04.40,Default,,0,0,0,,affects the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:04.40,0:18:05.77,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a field effect.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:05.77,0:18:11.02,Default,,0,0,0,,They decide to lead a contemplative lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:11.02,0:18:18.04,Default,,0,0,0,,You see, people chop up spirituality into intense meditation, and then back to usual,
Dialogue: 0,0:18:18.04,0:18:23.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and then some prayer meeting, and then back to usual, and it doesn't really work that
Dialogue: 0,0:18:23.46,0:18:24.46,Default,,0,0,0,,way.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:24.46,0:18:26.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It...
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.00,0:18:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The enthusiasms come and go.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:26.75,0:18:27.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:27.75,0:18:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:28.75,0:18:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:30.50,0:18:32.40,Default,,0,0,0,,And it's a lifestyle.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:32.40,0:18:40.98,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a lifestyle, which is oriented towards the realization of spiritual truth from within.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:40.98,0:18:46.95,Default,,0,0,0,,You mentioned contemplative means, like you can pick a phrase.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:46.95,0:18:55.02,Default,,0,0,0,,I did a, I think I spent a month originally on the 91st Psalm to contemplate it for, and
Dialogue: 0,0:18:55.02,0:18:57.13,Default,,0,0,0,,then its truth reveals itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:18:57.13,0:19:00.59,Default,,0,0,0,,So you don't try to understand it with the intellect.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:00.59,0:19:02.85,Default,,0,0,0,,And what happens is you hold it in mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:02.85,0:19:10.96,Default,,0,0,0,,divinity like reveals to you. So you're riding the subway and all of a sudden the whole subway
Dialogue: 0,0:19:10.96,0:19:18.24,Default,,0,0,0,,is transformed and it comes out of nowhere. It doesn't come about as linear thinking or
Dialogue: 0,0:19:18.24,0:19:26.38,Default,,0,0,0,,logic. However, in the lectures we try to tie the as yet unknown to the known. So we
Dialogue: 0,0:19:26.38,0:19:32.98,Default,,0,0,0,,try to connect it with archaeology and biology and evolution and mathematics and science
Dialogue: 0,0:19:32.98,0:19:44.04,Default,,0,0,0,,and logic and quantum mechanics. And so it's like planted, the roots are in the known.
Dialogue: 0,0:19:44.04,0:19:51.47,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you can see how it evolves and then you don't have to think about it, you just
Dialogue: 0,0:19:51.47,0:20:08.61,Default,,0,0,0,,know it. So the next slide. So all the levels have an attraction and an aversion. What keeps
Dialogue: 0,0:20:08.61,0:20:09.20,Default,,0,0,0,,the experience?
Dialogue: 0,0:20:09.22,0:20:17.69,Default,,0,0,0,,We talked about what is the ego? The ego experientially is the experiencer. Like the leading edge
Dialogue: 0,0:20:17.69,0:20:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,of the ego is very much like the shellfish at the bottom of the sea. It's out there,
Dialogue: 0,0:20:24.93,0:20:31.70,Default,,0,0,0,,it's like a probe. And it's always seeking, experiencing. So instead of worrying about
Dialogue: 0,0:20:31.70,0:20:39.50,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole ego, you just worry about the experiencer. The experiencer is where you have invested
Dialogue: 0,0:20:39.50,0:20:40.50,Default,,0,0,0,,your energy.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:40.75,0:20:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,And your identification is not with the whole ego, it's really just with the experiencer.
Dialogue: 0,0:20:51.42,0:21:00.41,Default,,0,0,0,,The experiencer is always searching for a payoff, no matter what the situation. It's
Dialogue: 0,0:21:00.41,0:21:12.82,Default,,0,0,0,,looking for a gain. The experiencer is like a screen. And it is one ten-thousandth of a
Dialogue: 0,0:21:12.82,0:21:23.04,Default,,0,0,0,,second removed from the reality. Therefore, the ego never experiences what is. It experiences
Dialogue: 0,0:21:23.43,0:21:30.64,Default,,0,0,0,,only what is the experience of what is. Therefore, it's not experiencing that which is being
Dialogue: 0,0:21:30.64,0:21:40.94,Default,,0,0,0,,recorded, it's experiencing the playback of the tape recorder. You know, on a tape recorder.
Dialogue: 0,0:21:40.94,0:21:50.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You can plug it in and hear what was just recorded. So the ego is experiencing that
Dialogue: 0,0:21:50.19,0:21:57.29,Default,,0,0,0,,which was just recorded. One ten-thousandth of a second ago. Hm, it doesn't seem like
Dialogue: 0,0:21:57.35,0:22:04.41,Default,,0,0,0,,much, except that the quality changes completely. This side of the one 10,000th of a second,
Dialogue: 0,0:22:05.57,0:22:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the trees look like trees. They look like flowers. And the other side of that one 10,000th
Dialogue: 0,0:22:14.21,0:22:24.02,Default,,0,0,0,,of a second, they radiate out divinity. And that gets screened out because the TV station
Dialogue: 0,0:22:24.02,0:22:31.63,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't record those qualities. It records linearity and emotion, like I watch in regular
Dialogue: 0,0:22:31.63,0:22:40.90,Default,,0,0,0,,television. Enlightenment is to bypass the experiencer. The experiencer just suddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:22:40.90,0:22:47.70,Default,,0,0,0,,goes out like that. It doesn't get weaker and weaker and weaker. It just suddenly out.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:48.96,0:22:51.46,Default,,0,0,0,,And then the mind goes silent in awe.
Dialogue: 0,0:22:56.08,0:23:05.07,Default,,0,0,0,,So, in the books I've...
Dialogue: 0,0:23:05.09,0:23:13.50,Default,,0,0,0,,This is finished. The focus of the whole chapter is on the experiencer. So, the experiencer
Dialogue: 0,0:23:13.50,0:23:22.51,Default,,0,0,0,,is always seeking. And it's seeking experience. So, the gain that you have to surrender is
Dialogue: 0,0:23:22.51,0:23:33.57,Default,,0,0,0,,experiencing itself, which the ego will not go along with. It will not readily extinguish
Dialogue: 0,0:23:33.57,0:23:34.07,Default,,0,0,0,,itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.55,0:23:37.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:23:37.98,0:23:43.66,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to bait it up a little bit, threaten it. Anyway. So, the experiencer is the leading
Dialogue: 0,0:23:43.66,0:23:51.22,Default,,0,0,0,,edge of awareness. The experiencer is like an information probe. So, you see, for life
Dialogue: 0,0:23:51.22,0:23:59.11,Default,,0,0,0,,to survive, it had to constantly obtain data. Edible, not edible. Friend, foe. You know
Dialogue: 0,0:23:59.11,0:24:05.74,Default,,0,0,0,,what I mean? It had to sense its environment. It had to imitate the environment. The octopus
Dialogue: 0,0:24:05.74,0:24:08.48,Default,,0,0,0,,or some other animal at the bottom of the ocean. It had to sense its environment. It had to
Dialogue: 0,0:24:08.50,0:24:14.50,Default,,0,0,0,,see, you know, is full of spiritual wisdom. They're great things to watch. Because suddenly
Dialogue: 0,0:24:14.50,0:24:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,it reveals to you the innate intelligence of creation. And it's discernment of beauty
Dialogue: 0,0:24:21.11,0:24:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and line. It's aesthetic. You look at the creatures, the incredible beauty of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:26.75,0:24:32.07,Default,,0,0,0,,You know? They didn't just come out in crazy blobs like this. They came out in a couple.
Dialogue: 0,0:24:32.07,0:24:38.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at the face of a tiger. Man, it's like a... What a creative genius. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:24:38.88,0:24:50.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. Where were we? Before we get carried away by the tiger. Do not play with tigers,
Dialogue: 0,0:24:50.46,0:24:59.08,Default,,0,0,0,,by the way. You know? Admire them from a distance. Okay. So, this is general attraction and aversion
Dialogue: 0,0:24:59.08,0:25:05.00,Default,,0,0,0,,applicable to the entire, all of the ego's programs. Then the next one after this, we
Dialogue: 0,0:25:05.00,0:25:11.45,Default,,0,0,0,,will start at the bottom of the list and see how it applies specifically to shame. You
Dialogue: 0,0:25:11.47,0:25:18.83,Default,,0,0,0,,know? This is the generality. And then we'll do, we'll apply these concepts to each level
Dialogue: 0,0:25:18.83,0:25:28.04,Default,,0,0,0,,of consciousness. And you begin to sort of intuit how it, how it all takes its place
Dialogue: 0,0:25:28.04,0:25:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in the psychic economy. The attraction is always to that which is familiar. First thing
Dialogue: 0,0:25:34.44,0:25:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,you do when you come into a crowd, you look around for a familiar face, right? The aversion
Dialogue: 0,0:25:39.71,0:25:44.49,Default,,0,0,0,,is to uncertainty. I mean, what if I go there and I don't see anybody I know?
Dialogue: 0,0:25:44.60,0:25:56.83,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh? Therefore, we cling to that which is known and are really actually fearful of
Dialogue: 0,0:25:56.83,0:26:03.48,Default,,0,0,0,,the future. The past is like certainty and the future is uncertainty. And the ego likes
Dialogue: 0,0:26:03.48,0:26:12.39,Default,,0,0,0,,to be certain. So, it doesn't like, it doesn't really like the new. The ego's attracted to
Dialogue: 0,0:26:12.39,0:26:19.97,Default,,0,0,0,,what's easy and has an aversion to effort. It's easier just to go along with some old
Dialogue: 0,0:26:19.97,0:26:20.39,Default,,0,0,0,,way.
Dialogue: 0,0:26:20.58,0:26:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,And then to put forth effort. So, we're going to look today at how to decrease effort so
Dialogue: 0,0:26:27.64,0:26:36.29,Default,,0,0,0,,that aversion doesn't prevail to the same degree. It's a resistance, okay? Because attention
Dialogue: 0,0:26:36.29,0:26:43.63,Default,,0,0,0,,begins to diminish a thing automatically. If you want to reduce the number of cookies
Dialogue: 0,0:26:43.63,0:26:50.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you eat every day, let's say you've been eating, overeating cookies for 20 years. Now, I'm
Dialogue: 0,0:26:50.42,0:26:52.24,Default,,0,0,0,,going to quit cookies someday. You never, you're not going to do that. You're going
Dialogue: 0,0:26:52.24,0:27:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,to quit cookies. You're lying to yourself. You are not going to quit cookies. You've
Dialogue: 0,0:27:00.44,0:27:06.57,Default,,0,0,0,,been eating 50 cookies a day for 20 years. You are not going to quit cookies. Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,0:27:06.57,0:27:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,I tell people, don't waste your seeming willpower which is going to bring you guilt and feeling
Dialogue: 0,0:27:10.90,0:27:16.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of failure. Don't bother. What you do is you merely start counting the cookies you eat
Dialogue: 0,0:27:16.77,0:27:25.73,Default,,0,0,0,,every day, but don't try to do anything about it. No. So, you lay out the cookies, 20 in
Dialogue: 0,0:27:26.52,0:27:37.77,Default,,0,0,0,,a day, the end of the day you count how many cookies you ate. 68. Tuesday, 64 cookies.
Dialogue: 0,0:27:37.77,0:27:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Thursday, a bad day, 72. Now, I don't want you to try to do anything about it. That's
Dialogue: 0,0:27:47.33,0:27:52.90,Default,,0,0,0,,the whole point. And enlightenment is very easy. It's a letting go and everybody struggles
Dialogue: 0,0:27:52.90,0:27:57.00,Default,,0,0,0,,and struggles. And then, finally one day you let go and the whole thing will
Dialogue: 0,0:27:57.00,0:27:58.33,Default,,0,0,0,,like such a...
Dialogue: 0,0:27:58.33,0:28:01.49,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I want you to just pay attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:02.47,0:28:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,So anything you don't like about yourself,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:04.65,0:28:07.34,Default,,0,0,0,,you just note down how many times a day you do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:08.25,0:28:11.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Getting annoyed with people, swearing, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:11.52,0:28:13.89,Default,,0,0,0,,hit your thumb, oh, Jesus Christ, oh, God, I'm sorry,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:14.02,0:28:14.60,Default,,0,0,0,,please forgive me.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:15.60,0:28:17.50,Default,,0,0,0,,How many times you swore today?
Dialogue: 0,0:28:18.39,0:28:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, you just start tracking it and paying attention.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.17,0:28:22.84,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:22.95,0:28:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Just notice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:25.26,0:28:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Now, don't tell me you can't do it
Dialogue: 0,0:28:26.75,0:28:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,because anybody can notice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:28.25,0:28:30.10,Default,,0,0,0,,You notice that you're eating 100 cookies a day,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:30.17,0:28:31.19,Default,,0,0,0,,that's why you're worrying about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:31.19,0:28:33.22,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course you can notice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:33.27,0:28:35.24,Default,,0,0,0,,So all you have to do is make a mental note
Dialogue: 0,0:28:35.24,0:28:37.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and write it down on a calendar.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:38.57,0:28:40.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Monday, 63 cookies.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:41.38,0:28:43.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Tuesday, 18 cookies.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:43.27,0:28:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:44.25,0:28:47.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And then Wednesday, back to usual, 58 cookies.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:48.55,0:28:52.68,Default,,0,0,0,,What will happen is by virtue of intention,
Dialogue: 0,0:28:52.94,0:28:55.88,Default,,0,0,0,,effortlessly, the Heisenberg principle begins to apply.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:56.88,0:28:59.20,Default,,0,0,0,,Awareness itself begins to diminish it.
Dialogue: 0,0:28:59.75,0:29:02.55,Default,,0,0,0,,By the end of a month, you'll be down to 14 cookies.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:03.29,0:29:04.48,Default,,0,0,0,,At the end of another month or two,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:04.57,0:29:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll be down to 16 cookies.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:07.22,0:29:08.18,Default,,0,0,0,,Six cookies, I mean.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:08.83,0:29:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And all of a sudden, you say,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:10.25,0:29:11.53,Default,,0,0,0,,what the F, I don't need cookies.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:14.35,0:29:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,It was all effortless.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:16.14,0:29:18.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to struggle, sackcloth and ashes,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:19.90,0:29:23.72,Default,,0,0,0,,cudgel yourself, manipulate yourself with guilt.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:24.79,0:29:27.31,Default,,0,0,0,,You just notice, just notice.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:27.31,0:29:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you notice it effortlessly,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:30.81,0:29:33.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the Heisenberg principle begins to apply.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.27,0:29:33.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:33.64,0:29:35.51,Default,,0,0,0,,Because by your intention, you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:36.25,0:29:39.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you've done is finessed the power of the field
Dialogue: 0,0:29:39.40,0:29:41.68,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of relying on the ego.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:42.72,0:29:44.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the field do it.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:44.57,0:29:45.59,Default,,0,0,0,,You pay your taxes?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:45.79,0:29:46.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What the hell?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:50.63,0:29:54.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Let the, the government's supposed to do it, ain't it?
Dialogue: 0,0:29:54.61,0:29:55.72,Default,,0,0,0,,So the field's the government.
Dialogue: 0,0:29:56.00,0:29:57.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You just show the government what your problem is,
Dialogue: 0,0:29:58.46,0:30:00.01,Default,,0,0,0,,and the government's going to take care of it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:00.01,0:30:00.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:02.85,0:30:04.55,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so you call in the government,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:05.29,0:30:06.20,Default,,0,0,0,,and you do that.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:06.27,0:30:09.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And you do that by the Heisenberg principle,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:09.49,0:30:10.47,Default,,0,0,0,,which is effortless.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:11.30,0:30:14.94,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is note it.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:15.05,0:30:16.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Pay attention, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:30:16.46,0:30:18.70,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's actually easy,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:18.83,0:30:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,but you avoid it because it seems like effort,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:20.77,0:30:22.48,Default,,0,0,0,,because you're going at it the hard way,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:23.09,0:30:25.00,Default,,0,0,0,,trying to lift yourself by your bootstraps.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:26.60,0:30:28.75,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction of anger is because
Dialogue: 0,0:30:28.75,0:30:30.76,Default,,0,0,0,,it feels to people like strength.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:32.14,0:30:33.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Of course, it's illusory.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:35.00,0:30:38.20,Default,,0,0,0,,However, the animal swells up with anger,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.20,0:30:38.88,Default,,0,0,0,,tries to intimidate,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:38.88,0:30:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,and tries to intimidate others.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:40.53,0:30:45.81,Default,,0,0,0,,And the aversion, the fear is of being seen passive or weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:45.88,0:30:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Being seen passive or weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:48.39,0:30:52.54,Default,,0,0,0,,In certain cultures, that'll get you killed, too.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:52.54,0:30:54.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Being seen as passive or weak,
Dialogue: 0,0:30:54.39,0:30:57.21,Default,,0,0,0,,we're experiencing that in other parts of the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:30:57.21,0:31:00.70,Default,,0,0,0,,If you're seen as passive or weak, they kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:00.70,0:31:03.74,Default,,0,0,0,,And certain neighborhoods in the inner city,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:03.74,0:31:06.35,Default,,0,0,0,,allowing yourself to be dissed,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:06.35,0:31:09.17,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the last thing you remember.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:09.17,0:31:10.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Allowing yourself to be dissed,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:10.84,0:31:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,is fatal.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:11.84,0:31:15.56,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the reality above 200 is totally different
Dialogue: 0,0:31:15.56,0:31:17.60,Default,,0,0,0,,than the reality below 200.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:17.60,0:31:22.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The naivete, the political naivete especially,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:22.60,0:31:27.96,Default,,0,0,0,,is to presume that other people are the way you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:27.96,0:31:29.81,Default,,0,0,0,,They are not.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:29.81,0:31:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,They are the opposite.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:33.89,0:31:35.58,Default,,0,0,0,,You think it's good to pay your bills,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:35.58,0:31:39.05,Default,,0,0,0,,they think you're an idiot for doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:39.05,0:31:40.70,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:40.70,0:31:42.81,Default,,0,0,0,,You think telling the truth is integrous,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:42.81,0:31:44.70,Default,,0,0,0,,and they think it's being stupid.
Dialogue: 0,0:31:44.70,0:31:52.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, therefore, strength then,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:52.53,0:31:56.90,Default,,0,0,0,,anger is seductive and addictive,
Dialogue: 0,0:31:56.90,0:32:00.51,Default,,0,0,0,,because you puff up, the animal puffs up,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:00.51,0:32:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and the fear is being seen passive or weak.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:05.81,0:32:07.16,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:07.16,0:32:11.16,Default,,0,0,0,,It's important here to win, and the dread is losing.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:13.25,0:32:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not aware of win-win.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:14.98,0:32:17.05,Default,,0,0,0,,In a dualistic world, one wins,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:17.05,0:32:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and the other one loses.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:19.19,0:32:23.77,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a materialistic, linear perception.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:23.77,0:32:29.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmically, a loss may be the biggest gain of your life,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:29.11,0:32:32.81,Default,,0,0,0,,because the world is what it is.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:32.81,0:32:37.84,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the optimum theater for karmic benefit.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:37.89,0:32:42.45,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the optimum place for the undoing of negative karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:42.45,0:32:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,and the gaining of positive karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:44.90,0:32:47.33,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, wanting to change the world
Dialogue: 0,0:32:47.33,0:32:48.68,Default,,0,0,0,,doesn't make much sense.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:48.68,0:32:52.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, Ramana Maharaja, she says,
Dialogue: 0,0:32:52.92,0:32:55.66,Default,,0,0,0,,the world you see doesn't even exist.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:55.66,0:32:58.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Save yourself the trouble and surrender to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:32:58.88,0:33:02.00,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if the purpose of the world is to provide
Dialogue: 0,0:33:02.00,0:33:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,an optimum opportunity for the undoing of negative karma,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:06.98,0:33:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,all your do-gooderism is gonna sentence those people
Dialogue: 0,0:33:10.90,0:33:14.63,Default,,0,0,0,,to a continuation of bad karma, is it not?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:14.63,0:33:16.45,Default,,0,0,0,,They can't kill themself on the streetcar.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:16.45,0:33:17.43,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll do it on the bus.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:17.43,0:33:18.56,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll drive off with it.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:20.16,0:33:22.25,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:22.25,0:33:28.25,Default,,0,0,0,,So, all right, win and lose is the ego's perception,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:28.25,0:33:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,because you don't know what seeming loss
Dialogue: 0,0:33:31.64,0:33:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is gonna be a tremendous gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:34.69,0:33:38.45,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't know what seeming loss is gonna open the door.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:38.45,0:33:42.67,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it's by loss that the doorway to the new is open,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:42.67,0:33:44.50,Default,,0,0,0,,because otherwise, the ego's gonna constantly
Dialogue: 0,0:33:44.50,0:33:46.19,Default,,0,0,0,,cling to the past.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:46.19,0:33:47.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's gonna cling to the familiar,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:47.65,0:33:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and we'll never know what freedom is like.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:52.27,0:33:53.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:33:53.27,0:33:56.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The idea that you have to be important,
Dialogue: 0,0:33:56.01,0:33:58.18,Default,,0,0,0,,and here you might be nobody, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:33:59.16,0:34:00.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You gotta be noticed,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:00.42,0:34:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and that's the whole world of glamor, to be noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:04.77,0:34:07.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the basic here thing about the ego,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:07.55,0:34:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,which has been ever since the beginning of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:10.67,0:34:13.48,Default,,0,0,0,,is it constantly seeks for gain,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:13.48,0:34:15.40,Default,,0,0,0,,and its fear is one of loss.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:15.40,0:34:17.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It clutches.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:17.03,0:34:21.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the ego is characterized by clutching this.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:21.05,0:34:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to control.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:24.30,0:34:27.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute the ego thinks a thing is mine,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:27.63,0:34:29.23,Default,,0,0,0,,it totally changes dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:31.42,0:34:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The magic of mine instantly changes it.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:37.44,0:34:41.80,Default,,0,0,0,,That's just a watch, but if it's my watch,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:41.80,0:34:44.65,Default,,0,0,0,,uh-oh, now it's special.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:44.65,0:34:47.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's my sentimental watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:47.57,0:34:50.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's old granddad's watch.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:50.30,0:34:54.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, wow, now it begins, it's ego, you know,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:54.17,0:34:56.19,Default,,0,0,0,,it's ego inflation.
Dialogue: 0,0:34:56.19,0:34:59.65,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you add mine, therefore, the body should be,
Dialogue: 0,0:34:59.65,0:35:02.84,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, I think, a new nature.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:02.84,0:35:04.01,Default,,0,0,0,,And, uh, by the way,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:04.01,0:35:07.09,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm actually referring to it as an it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:07.09,0:35:12.32,Default,,0,0,0,,Whatever it's doing is really not all that interesting
Dialogue: 0,0:35:12.32,0:35:14.11,Default,,0,0,0,,if you watch it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:15.11,0:35:17.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It, it does what it's supposed to do.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:17.76,0:35:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,And when the ego sort of resolves
Dialogue: 0,0:35:20.03,0:35:22.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and is just sort of a oneness,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:22.46,0:35:27.44,Default,,0,0,0,,uh, you watch it walking around,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:27.44,0:35:28.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's like a wind-up toy.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:28.57,0:35:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it's still, you see it's still doing it.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:31.82,0:35:34.11,Default,,0,0,0,,For decades, it just wanders, it walks around by itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:34.11,0:35:35.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It does whatever it's gonna do.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:35.65,0:35:37.03,Default,,0,0,0,,It points with this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:37.15,0:35:40.13,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want anything to do with it, but it goes on its own.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:41.98,0:35:45.38,Default,,0,0,0,,To win and lose, importance, the idea.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:45.53,0:35:51.17,Default,,0,0,0,,So if you say my body or my mind, my possessions,
Dialogue: 0,0:35:52.13,0:35:55.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the minute you add the word my, you're stuck.
Dialogue: 0,0:35:56.92,0:35:59.38,Default,,0,0,0,,First of all, nothing belongs to you, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:00.63,0:36:02.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything belongs to God.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:03.67,0:36:07.84,Default,,0,0,0,,You have temporary custody, temporary custody.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:07.84,0:36:10.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You are the steward of these things.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:11.86,0:36:14.73,Default,,0,0,0,,See yourself as the steward rather than the owner.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:16.36,0:36:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It's the body and it's the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:20.61,0:36:22.71,Default,,0,0,0,,And when you stop referring to it as me,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:23.48,0:36:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,it loses its attractive ego investment.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:28.09,0:36:32.65,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a body and it's the body and it's the mind.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:35.00,0:36:39.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, to be hypnotized by the mind is to think these are my thoughts.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:39.50,0:36:43.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The thoughts emanate.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:43.59,0:36:46.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The thoughts emanate from the field of consciousness impersonally.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:48.44,0:36:50.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The minute you connect with a certain level of consciousness,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:51.26,0:36:53.38,Default,,0,0,0,,you're connected to an attractor field.
Dialogue: 0,0:36:53.59,0:36:57.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That attractor field has the same thoughts and has always had them,
Dialogue: 0,0:36:58.82,0:37:00.23,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, for thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:02.65,0:37:03.86,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing novel about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:05.00,0:37:07.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It's mine and I'll kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:07.82,0:37:08.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You think that's your thought?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:09.53,0:37:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Did you invent that thought?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:11.57,0:37:13.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Something new in man's history?
Dialogue: 0,0:37:16.21,0:37:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That prevailing thought field,
Dialogue: 0,0:37:18.50,0:37:19.50,Default,,0,0,0,,thinks that way.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:20.19,0:37:22.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Those thoughts belong to the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:22.19,0:37:23.19,Default,,0,0,0,,They're not yours.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:23.82,0:37:29.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So don't claim ownership for that which or over which you have no ownership.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:31.00,0:37:32.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Nothing belongs to anyone.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:33.59,0:37:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Everything belongs to divinity.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:36.50,0:37:39.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You have temporary custody, temporary stewardship.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:40.51,0:37:45.15,Default,,0,0,0,,So to give up your life for something which isn't even yours is a little ridiculous, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:48.05,0:37:49.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, Lord.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:50.51,0:37:54.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So the importance, then, is, this is self-importance.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:56.05,0:37:58.40,Default,,0,0,0,,So the ego is designed to gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:37:59.01,0:38:01.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Money, of course, is a very big one.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:01.65,0:38:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Money, excitement, all these things are very big.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:05.59,0:38:09.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When we get to the levels of consciousness correlating with happiness,
Dialogue: 0,0:38:09.63,0:38:15.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you will notice that happiness is almost one to one correlated with level of consciousness and with nothing else.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:16.61,0:38:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It does not correlate with wealth, not even correlated with health, not correlated with success.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:22.90,0:38:24.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It's correlated with level of consciousness.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:24.82,0:38:26.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Period.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:28.13,0:38:29.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Period, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:29.92,0:38:33.46,Default,,0,0,0,,So just advance your consciousness and think of all the work you saved yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:39.44,0:38:42.78,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, you know, you can be delighted with nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:44.13,0:38:45.50,Default,,0,0,0,,The less you've got, the better.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:45.51,0:38:53.19,Default,,0,0,0,,You can live with a cot, a blanket you got from the Goodwill, a box, an apple and a six pack of Pepsi.
Dialogue: 0,0:38:53.19,0:39:00.78,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:00.78,0:39:01.01,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.01,0:39:01.26,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:01.26,0:39:01.94,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.30,0:39:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:02.38,0:39:07.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And to add to your heavenly abode, you get a cat.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:08.05,0:39:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Now you've got everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:09.32,0:39:14.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You've got a piece of cheese, some Pepsi, a cat, a cot, and a candle.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:15.09,0:39:15.50,Default,,0,0,0,,There you go.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:18.09,0:39:19.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you need anything to read? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:19.34,0:39:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you need television? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:21.65,0:39:22.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you need a radio? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:22.82,0:39:24.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Do you need to read the paper? No.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:28.17,0:39:30.80,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't even know Regan had been shot for weeks later.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:32.51,0:39:34.44,Default,,0,0,0,,A coffee shop, somebody mentioned Regan.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:34.76,0:39:35.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't say.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:37.76,0:39:38.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:38.86,0:39:43.11,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't say Regan who, I said Regan him.
Dialogue: 0,0:39:43.11,0:39:49.86,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the ego is invested in all these various levels,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:50.46,0:39:54.19,Default,,0,0,0,,with being important, being noticed, with gain, it fears loss,
Dialogue: 0,0:39:54.69,0:39:58.23,Default,,0,0,0,,and money is the magical road to happiness, money.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:00.98,0:40:04.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The experiencer, in order to justify its own existence,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:05.59,0:40:08.28,Default,,0,0,0,,seeks the energy that it pulls out of excitement,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:09.17,0:40:12.09,Default,,0,0,0,,and it dreads boredom, dreads boredom.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:13.50,0:40:14.90,Default,,0,0,0,,The way out of boredom is to lie.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:14.92,0:40:21.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Allow yourself to be bored, and then investigate why you feel bored and what that emotion is.
Dialogue: 0,0:40:22.63,0:40:30.36,Default,,0,0,0,,If you want to discover what the experiencer does, allow yourself to, instead of escapism,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:30.96,0:40:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,allow yourself to be bored and just contemplate on what is boredom, and what is it I'm experiencing,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:38.96,0:40:40.65,Default,,0,0,0,,and why do I have an aversion to it?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:43.92,0:40:47.15,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a very rapid way to find out exactly what the experiencer is,
Dialogue: 0,0:40:47.80,0:40:50.59,Default,,0,0,0,,what it does, and what it subserves, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:51.80,0:40:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,What is, and then you say, well, what is it that's bored?
Dialogue: 0,0:40:56.57,0:41:02.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What, what is it, what aspect of myself is it that's bored, and complaining, and what is it complaining of?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:03.53,0:41:05.09,Default,,0,0,0,,There's nothing interesting going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:10.23,0:41:11.96,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I get out of interest?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:13.55,0:41:15.63,Default,,0,0,0,,What do I get out of things that are interesting?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:16.80,0:41:21.11,Default,,0,0,0,,A sense of aliveness and excitement of the spirit or of the ego?
Dialogue: 0,0:41:21.53,0:41:23.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh, so you see.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:23.05,0:41:29.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Uh-huh, it's the animal, uh, wanting constant entertainment.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:30.57,0:41:35.42,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, it likes excitement, and it dreads boredom, because boredom is almost like death.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:36.40,0:41:40.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It works off desire, and it has afraid, fears it won't get.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:41.21,0:41:44.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It looks for status, and fears being a nobody.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:45.21,0:41:48.28,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to be noticed, and is afraid it'll be ignored.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:49.80,0:41:54.88,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to express its opinions about everything, and it dreads just being ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:41:55.61,0:42:00.11,Default,,0,0,0,,Free speech is today's circus, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:01.11,0:42:05.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I had a good friend I knew for many years, and he came to me one day, and he said,
Dialogue: 0,0:42:05.51,0:42:07.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I just made the most amazing discovery.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:07.51,0:42:08.51,Default,,0,0,0,,I said, what is it?
Dialogue: 0,0:42:08.51,0:42:11.55,Default,,0,0,0,,He says, I don't have to have an opinion on everything.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:17.42,0:42:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,He said, I never experienced such freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:19.42,0:42:23.61,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I, no, I don't have a view, have to have a viewpoint, I don't have to have an opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:24.71,0:42:28.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't feel called upon to express my free speech, take a stand, and get out there with a placard.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:29.61,0:42:33.61,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it was freedom.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:33.61,0:42:37.50,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:37.50,0:42:42.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Not, you don't have to have an opinion, and it's okay to be ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:42.50,0:42:45.05,Default,,0,0,0,,It's okay to be ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:45.05,0:42:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, it's really good to be ordinary.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:48.05,0:42:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,For, when they're looking for who to shoot, it just pays off.
Dialogue: 0,0:42:54.46,0:43:01.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Why is it, you with the pink mustache and the red hair sitting on you, come over here, you son of a .
Dialogue: 0,0:43:01.78,0:43:02.78,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:02.78,0:43:04.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:04.23,0:43:05.23,Default,,0,0,0,,No, you want to blend in.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:05.23,0:43:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,My survival technique when I was young was to blend in with the woodwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:12.01,0:43:14.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Blend in with the woodwork.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:14.42,0:43:19.42,Default,,0,0,0,,In boot camp, it's 10 below zero in Great Lakes, pitch black in the morning.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:19.42,0:43:21.55,Default,,0,0,0,,They get you all up.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:21.55,0:43:26.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You got to run around the thing a lap, a mile.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:26.76,0:43:28.96,Default,,0,0,0,,No breakfast, nothing.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:28.96,0:43:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,In the black, it's 10 below zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:32.53,0:43:36.53,Default,,0,0,0,,So, I discovered the way to do it is to just blend in and not be noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:36.53,0:43:39.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I had lockers, and you could open the locker, and as they went out.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:50.00,0:43:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,I did that all through boot camp.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:55.23,0:43:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,You just blend in.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:57.23,0:43:59.42,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll never notice you.
Dialogue: 0,0:43:59.42,0:44:03.42,Default,,0,0,0,,See, if they noticed you, they would be out in the field, and they'd say, where's Hawkins?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:03.42,0:44:04.42,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:04.42,0:44:07.42,Default,,0,0,0,,No, by being anonymous, you never notice it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:07.42,0:44:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,One time, I did get caught, and I had to do two laps around, but almost the whole time except that once.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:15.48,0:44:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:16.48,0:44:20.67,Default,,0,0,0,,The way to survive is to become invisible.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:20.67,0:44:21.67,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:21.67,0:44:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the value of camouflage.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:23.67,0:44:26.82,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, if you're aggressive, you stand out there, and you avoid aggression.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:26.82,0:44:27.82,Default,,0,0,0,,See?
Dialogue: 0,0:44:27.82,0:44:29.82,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you're good, well camouflaged.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:29.82,0:44:31.82,Default,,0,0,0,,That's why I'd like to be an octopus.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:31.82,0:44:35.82,Default,,0,0,0,,If I was going to be something, you'd just look like everything else around you.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:37.82,0:44:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:38.82,0:44:41.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So, we seek status.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:41.23,0:44:42.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to be noticed.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:42.23,0:44:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to have an opinion.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:44.23,0:44:47.23,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego is constantly craving things.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:47.23,0:44:49.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And it dreads frustration.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:49.23,0:44:51.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It dreads not having it.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:51.23,0:44:55.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And therefore, to achieve all of the above, it wants control.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:55.23,0:44:57.23,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants control.
Dialogue: 0,0:44:57.23,0:45:00.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And it has an aversion to accepting.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:00.44,0:45:13.19,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to control the world and control out there instead of change the world instead of changing yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:13.19,0:45:21.13,Default,,0,0,0,,If you don't like the world the way it is, then change yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:21.13,0:45:26.13,Default,,0,0,0,,Do the world a favor.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:26.13,0:45:33.98,Default,,0,0,0,,All the wondrous do-gooders, the great monarchs, the great rulers, all the do-gooders are dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:33.98,0:45:39.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Their dynasties are dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:39.63,0:45:43.90,Default,,0,0,0,,To establish the greatest nation on earth, they're all dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:43.90,0:45:46.09,Default,,0,0,0,,They're all dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:46.09,0:45:48.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All dead.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:48.09,0:45:52.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of changing the world, change yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:52.69,0:45:55.69,Default,,0,0,0,,If the word God over the courthouse makes you uncomfortable,
Dialogue: 0,0:45:55.69,0:45:58.15,Default,,0,0,0,,then change yourself.
Dialogue: 0,0:45:58.15,0:46:00.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Why would it make you uncomfortable?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:00.65,0:46:03.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And what do you care?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:03.98,0:46:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always protesters out about some issue that doesn't even involve their life.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:08.98,0:46:12.51,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all in their head, you know?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:12.51,0:46:14.51,Default,,0,0,0,,All in their head.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:14.51,0:46:16.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:16.88,0:46:20.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, it craves and what it wants is control.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:20.03,0:46:26.03,Default,,0,0,0,,So, one of the biggest surrenders you can make is letting go of wanting to control things.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:26.03,0:46:28.03,Default,,0,0,0,,Letting go of wanting to control.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:28.03,0:46:32.26,Default,,0,0,0,,Because evolution is evolving in a certain way,
Dialogue: 0,0:46:32.26,0:46:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and therefore to try and control it, you don't even know what you're asking for.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:37.76,0:46:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,You know, you're grabbing onto a high voltage wire the minute you try to control things.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:42.76,0:46:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And the karmic consequences are...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:45.76,0:46:49.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So, the best wisdom is to surrender it to God as...
Dialogue: 0,0:46:49.76,0:46:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Surrender the world to God, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:46:51.76,0:46:55.36,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego doesn't like that.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:55.36,0:46:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,The spiritual ego wants to save the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:58.69,0:46:59.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Save the world.
Dialogue: 0,0:46:59.69,0:47:02.36,Default,,0,0,0,,What are you going to save it from?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:07.03,0:47:08.03,Default,,0,0,0,,From what?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:08.03,0:47:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,The Buddha, Jesus Christ, all the great avatars,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:14.96,0:47:19.96,Default,,0,0,0,,said the only problem that exists in the world is ignorance.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:19.96,0:47:23.09,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if you're going to do anything for the world,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:23.09,0:47:28.19,Default,,0,0,0,,all you can do is try to educate and overcome ignorance, huh?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:28.19,0:47:32.51,Default,,0,0,0,,The world you see doesn't even exist, see?
Dialogue: 0,0:47:32.51,0:47:34.55,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it as injustices.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:35.55,0:47:38.55,Default,,0,0,0,,And that's from your position you see it as an injustice.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:38.55,0:47:43.71,Default,,0,0,0,,From this position over here, it is justice.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:43.71,0:47:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Interesting program the other night, very good one on slavery.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:49.44,0:47:53.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Best one I've never saw slavery explained that way, I think, on the History Channel.
Dialogue: 0,0:47:53.44,0:47:59.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Contextualize it in terms of the economics of the day,
Dialogue: 0,0:47:59.07,0:48:03.07,Default,,0,0,0,,the religious beliefs of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:03.07,0:48:06.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The United States had more money invested in slaves
Dialogue: 0,0:48:06.07,0:48:08.07,Default,,0,0,0,,than in any other industry.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:08.07,0:48:12.07,Default,,0,0,0,,It was the biggest industry of the entire economy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:12.07,0:48:16.46,Default,,0,0,0,,All different aspects, which I'd never seen before
Dialogue: 0,0:48:16.46,0:48:20.46,Default,,0,0,0,,until it was contextualized from a greater dimension.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:20.46,0:48:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Its economic weight, its impact on just about every aspect of society.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:26.78,0:48:35.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, relinquishing it was not just a religious belief of equality,
Dialogue: 0,0:48:35.78,0:48:41.78,Default,,0,0,0,,it had to do with pulling the drain on the entire economy.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:41.78,0:48:44.78,Default,,0,0,0,,So now you understand it a little bit differently.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:44.78,0:48:47.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You feel a little less judgmental about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:47.78,0:48:51.59,Default,,0,0,0,,All those bad southerners and all this.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:51.59,0:48:54.59,Default,,0,0,0,,And when it's recontextualized, now it takes on a different significance
Dialogue: 0,0:48:54.59,0:48:57.75,Default,,0,0,0,,and a different meaning, different meaning.
Dialogue: 0,0:48:57.75,0:49:00.75,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so it was the economy of the day.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:00.75,0:49:07.07,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego likes novelty, hates boredom and sameness,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:07.07,0:49:10.15,Default,,0,0,0,,and it gets addicted to thrills.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:10.15,0:49:12.78,Default,,0,0,0,,A phrase that's going to miss out on something.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:12.78,0:49:14.78,Default,,0,0,0,,The sound of the motorcycle racing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:17.78,0:49:20.78,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a, come on boys, get into the excitement,
Dialogue: 0,0:49:20.78,0:49:22.78,Default,,0,0,0,,get into the risk, get into the danger.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:22.78,0:49:26.78,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, the novelty, addicted to thrills.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:26.78,0:49:30.01,Default,,0,0,0,,People will go to such extremes, it's mind-boggling.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:30.01,0:49:33.01,Default,,0,0,0,,This guy, this Frenchman that has a compulsion
Dialogue: 0,0:49:33.01,0:49:36.01,Default,,0,0,0,,to climb all the tallest buildings in all the major cities in Europe.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:36.01,0:49:38.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Like a human fly.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:38.01,0:49:42.01,Default,,0,0,0,,He goes up the other side of these marble buildings.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:42.01,0:49:45.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And they keep arresting him and bringing him down.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:45.78,0:49:49.78,Default,,0,0,0,,In China or someplace, they put him in jail and beat him with rods
Dialogue: 0,0:49:49.78,0:49:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,to make him stop doing this thing.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:51.78,0:49:53.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And he wouldn't stop.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:53.78,0:49:56.78,Default,,0,0,0,,As soon as he's out, he's back doing it again, you know.
Dialogue: 0,0:49:56.78,0:50:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:00.69,0:50:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So he has an addiction to the thrill.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:02.69,0:50:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction here is to be aggressive.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:05.46,0:50:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,The fear is passivity.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:07.46,0:50:09.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you want to gossip.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:09.71,0:50:10.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you're afraid you're going to be left out.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:10.71,0:50:13.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You're afraid you're going to be left out of what's going on.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:13.71,0:50:17.84,Default,,0,0,0,,The addiction to want to be fashionable instead of being drab.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:17.84,0:50:20.84,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, it's very necessary to be right.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:20.84,0:50:24.88,Default,,0,0,0,,In fact, being right is more important than life itself.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:24.88,0:50:27.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh yes.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:27.67,0:50:32.71,Default,,0,0,0,,People lay down their lives by the tens of millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:32.71,0:50:34.71,Default,,0,0,0,,By the tens of millions.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:34.71,0:50:39.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Whole generations, whole societies, whole cultures, whole nations.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:39.71,0:50:42.71,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather than admit they were wrong.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:42.71,0:50:45.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Isn't that something?
Dialogue: 0,0:50:45.55,0:50:48.80,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego's out to kill you.
Dialogue: 0,0:50:48.80,0:51:01.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Better to be dead and right than wrong and live.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:01.15,0:51:05.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize how powerful that is.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:05.48,0:51:11.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Whole regimes, whole political parties, multi-millionaires,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:11.48,0:51:16.65,Default,,0,0,0,,all kinds of people stake their entire life on being right.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:16.65,0:51:18.80,Default,,0,0,0,,And they will lie through their teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:18.80,0:51:21.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They will perjure themselves.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:21.07,0:51:25.07,Default,,0,0,0,,They'll put their hand on the Bible and swear to tell the truth.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:25.07,0:51:27.07,Default,,0,0,0,,And lie through their teeth.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:27.07,0:51:32.05,Default,,0,0,0,,When you know how to do kinesiology, it's always fun to watch the...
Dialogue: 0,0:51:32.05,0:51:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always a major mystery, murder on trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:37.05,0:51:42.05,Default,,0,0,0,,There's always somebody who's up on some kind of a major trial.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:42.05,0:51:46.05,Default,,0,0,0,,And of course, within seconds of kinesiology, you can tell whether they're guilty or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:46.05,0:51:47.05,Default,,0,0,0,,So this guy did it or not.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:47.05,0:51:48.05,Default,,0,0,0,,You got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:51:48.05,0:51:54.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's going to take these 12 people a couple million dollars worth of time,
Dialogue: 0,0:51:54.05,0:52:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,lawyer's fees and all, and you already got it.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:00.71,0:52:01.71,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:01.71,0:52:03.71,Default,,0,0,0,,So being right is very important.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:03.71,0:52:04.71,Default,,0,0,0,,To be superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:04.71,0:52:09.84,Default,,0,0,0,,Because by being right, you become superior and you dread being common.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:09.84,0:52:11.84,Default,,0,0,0,,What is that dread of being common?
Dialogue: 0,0:52:11.84,0:52:15.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Being looked over, not being special.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:15.19,0:52:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,If you let go of that one, you let go of the attraction of a lot of positions.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:19.19,0:52:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It's better to be anonymous.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:23.92,0:52:27.92,Default,,0,0,0,,You live a lot longer if nobody knows who the hell you are.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:31.53,0:52:35.53,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to go around the track at 10 below zero.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:40.76,0:52:41.76,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:41.76,0:52:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,So it wants to be superior.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:43.76,0:52:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,And for some reason, it just hates being common.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:46.76,0:52:51.78,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to speak up instead of shutting up.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:51.78,0:52:54.78,Default,,0,0,0,,99% of speech is really non-integrist.
Dialogue: 0,0:52:54.78,0:53:02.23,Default,,0,0,0,,If you calibrate the level of free speech as a concept, it's, like, I don't know, 340 or something.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:02.23,0:53:10.80,Default,,0,0,0,,If you calibrate it as it is practiced in the United States right now, it's about 187.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:10.80,0:53:17.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Now people talk about free speech as though that is the highest prize of civilization.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:17.82,0:53:19.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:19.28,0:53:21.28,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the highest prize of civilization?
Dialogue: 0,0:53:21.28,0:53:22.88,Default,,0,0,0,,That any idiot can go on TV and just...
Dialogue: 0,0:53:22.88,0:53:23.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Think about it.
Dialogue: 0,0:53:23.88,0:53:38.30,Default,,0,0,0,,on TV and just rattle away? Is that the highest good of mankind? Should we die for that? Speaking
Dialogue: 0,0:53:38.30,0:53:48.84,Default,,0,0,0,,up is usually about 99% ego and 1% fact. 1% fact. 1% fact. The rest is people like to hear themselves
Dialogue: 0,0:53:48.84,0:54:00.34,Default,,0,0,0,,talk. So being silent then is anathema to the ego. The ego is stubborn, hates to give in, wants to be
Dialogue: 0,0:54:00.34,0:54:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,famous, hates the idea of being anonymous. All right. The attraction to change here is resisting and to
Dialogue: 0,0:54:09.88,0:54:18.90,Default,,0,0,0,,defend your position rather than to give in because to give in is giving up being right. And it views
Dialogue: 0,0:54:18.90,0:54:20.75,Default,,0,0,0,,success as getting whatever you want.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:20.76,0:54:28.30,Default,,0,0,0,,But it wants. So whatever the ego decides it wants, that is success. And it believes that that is
Dialogue: 0,0:54:28.30,0:54:38.82,Default,,0,0,0,,happiness. More money, more sex, more whatever. The attraction to the ego is that of specialness. It
Dialogue: 0,0:54:38.82,0:54:46.30,Default,,0,0,0,,has an aversion to commonness. It wants more and is afraid of having less. I don't know. Didn't the
Dialogue: 0,0:54:46.30,0:54:51.94,Default,,0,0,0,,ego ever have less? I mean, it's great. Less. There's lots of things. Just think how wonderful it
Dialogue: 0,0:54:51.94,0:54:52.88,Default,,0,0,0,,would be if you had less of them.
Dialogue: 0,0:54:52.94,0:55:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. To own a thing then is its claim of specialness. And in reality, it doesn't want to look at the fact. It only has
Dialogue: 0,0:55:03.44,0:55:13.80,Default,,0,0,0,,temporary stewardship. No matter what you own, it's only a temporary stewardship. Temporary stewardship. You can't
Dialogue: 0,0:55:13.80,0:55:26.30,Default,,0,0,0,,actually own anything. To own it, you would have to be it. That's a nice idea of comprehension. To own this, I would have to be it.
Dialogue: 0,0:55:31.61,0:55:44.67,Default,,0,0,0,,What we have is a claim. Claim. The attraction is to attraction itself. The aversion is to plainness and ordinary words. The ego at the
Dialogue: 0,0:55:44.67,0:55:54.09,Default,,0,0,0,,wind would like to warp facts, and it really dislikes the truth. It dislikes the truth. We'll see what the reaction is to the book I
Dialogue: 0,0:55:54.09,0:56:04.26,Default,,0,0,0,,called Culting Truth vs. Walton. We'll see how popular the truth is, right?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:04.26,0:56:06.11,Default,,0,0,0,,When is it coming out?
Dialogue: 0,0:56:06.11,0:56:09.28,Default,,0,0,0,,A couple of weeks, a week or two. Soon, anyway.
Dialogue: 0,0:56:09.42,0:56:20.13,Default,,0,0,0,,All right. It wants to warp facts, and every night you can hear it on television. The interviewer asks the person the question. He doesn't
Dialogue: 0,0:56:20.13,0:56:34.40,Default,,0,0,0,,answer the question. He sidesteps it and gives you some alternate subject. You can tell he's a politician right away. The ego wants to
Dialogue: 0,0:56:34.40,0:56:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,condemn rather than forgive. So how can we forgive such violations of the truth? It's because we see that the
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.76,0:56:43.94,Default,,0,0,0,,ego wants to condemn rather than forgive. So how can we forgive such violations of the truth? It's because we see that the ego wants to
Dialogue: 0,0:56:43.96,0:56:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,condemn rather than forgive. So how can we forgive such violations of the truth? It's because we see that the ego, unabated, is addicted and has to win. It doesn't have
Dialogue: 0,0:56:49.53,0:56:51.71,Default,,0,0,0,,any choice. It chooses only
Dialogue: 0,0:56:51.71,0:57:03.21,Default,,0,0,0,,the good, and the good is to win. Therefore, we forgive the politician for lying through his teeth, with his hand on a bible
Dialogue: 0,0:57:03.21,0:57:11.80,Default,,0,0,0,,lying through his teeth. You say, God, the karma of that, you know when you get on the other side. When you get on the other side,
Dialogue: 0,0:57:11.80,0:57:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,we're spiritually aware.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:14.01,0:57:15.17,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.17,0:57:15.34,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.34,0:57:15.44,Default,,0,0,0,,.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:15.44,0:57:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So we know that there are karmic consequences.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:19.23,0:57:23.11,Default,,0,0,0,,To work the facts then is what politics is all about.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:24.23,0:57:28.28,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego wants to condemn rather than forgive.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:29.23,0:57:30.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't want to excuse.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:30.57,0:57:38.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And the populace has like a dread of what if a guilty guy goes free?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:42.23,0:57:46.71,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear almost a panic, emotional panic, that a guilty guy went free.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:47.59,0:57:47.94,Default,,0,0,0,,So?
Dialogue: 0,0:57:49.69,0:57:51.55,Default,,0,0,0,,So he went free, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:52.23,0:57:56.53,Default,,0,0,0,,He went free in the perceptual world, but he did not escape the karma.
Dialogue: 0,0:57:57.40,0:58:02.38,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, because, all right, so we can forgive.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:02.53,0:58:07.00,Default,,0,0,0,,Realize that people are driven by choosing what they see as the good,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:07.17,0:58:10.38,Default,,0,0,0,,and if the good is to win, they will sell their soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:10.65,0:58:11.59,Default,,0,0,0,,They will sell their soul.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:13.17,0:58:15.78,Default,,0,0,0,,You know the opera, Dr. Faustus.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:16.73,0:58:21.53,Default,,0,0,0,,Faustus sells out his integrity of his soul for temporary gain.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:22.36,0:58:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,And the end of the opera is payoff time.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:28.05,0:58:29.90,Default,,0,0,0,,And the door is the hell open.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:30.86,0:58:33.50,Default,,0,0,0,,And now, now it's time to pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:34.11,0:58:35.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Now it's time to pay.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:35.96,0:58:36.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, very interesting.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:37.11,0:58:38.07,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmically correct.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:38.28,0:58:39.78,Default,,0,0,0,,And if you calibrate it, it is true.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:40.90,0:58:44.23,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, it wants to hold on to things rather than let go.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:45.76,0:58:49.11,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to dominate rather than succumb.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:50.53,0:58:53.94,Default,,0,0,0,,It's interested in the linear content and not the field.
Dialogue: 0,0:58:54.53,0:58:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, to win an argument, you'll notice politically,
Dialogue: 0,0:58:58.96,0:59:01.05,Default,,0,0,0,,people always ignore the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:02.01,0:59:03.76,Default,,0,0,0,,They always ignore the context.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:06.67,0:59:10.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Because if they included context, what they're saying would be idiotic.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:15.19,0:59:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, I won't go into current examples, but they're pretty glaring.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:24.11,0:59:28.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants abundance and dislikes frugality.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:29.36,0:59:31.21,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to be the martyr.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:31.53,0:59:32.92,Default,,0,0,0,,If you can't win,
Dialogue: 0,0:59:33.34,0:59:37.05,Default,,0,0,0,,then you can still juice it by being the martyr and the loser.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:38.40,0:59:43.23,Default,,0,0,0,,And best of all, and very, the top of the popularity list is victim.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:44.36,0:59:47.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You get to be victim instead of being responsible.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:48.57,0:59:48.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:49.82,0:59:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's to blame?
Dialogue: 0,0:59:51.55,0:59:53.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It's funny, listen to the television.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:53.59,0:59:56.51,Default,,0,0,0,,You hear some catastrophic event.
Dialogue: 0,0:59:57.13,1:00:00.03,Default,,0,0,0,,The first thing the announcer says, who's to blame?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:02.38,1:00:05.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The Brooklyn Bridge fell down.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.32,1:00:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,Who's to blame?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:05.48,1:00:09.07,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, who cares who's to blame?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:10.01,1:00:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,But the vindictiveness of the ego,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:12.86,1:00:16.48,Default,,0,0,0,,it instantly looks for who are we going to blame,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:17.13,1:00:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and then we're going to hate them and take revenge on them and beat up.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:23.28,1:00:24.57,Default,,0,0,0,,That's the ego's game.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:25.36,1:00:27.32,Default,,0,0,0,,It loves to blame somebody,
Dialogue: 0,1:00:27.51,1:00:29.80,Default,,0,0,0,,because now you can guiltlessly hate them
Dialogue: 0,1:00:29.80,1:00:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and beat up on them and seek revenge.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:33.19,1:00:35.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You can electrocute them.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:35.13,1:00:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,That's cool.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:36.53,1:00:37.53,Default,,0,0,0,,That's a cool way to go.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:42.86,1:00:47.86,Default,,0,0,0,,It's never been demonstrated that capital punishment has prevented crime at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:49.40,1:00:54.82,Default,,0,0,0,,At one time, there were 300 different crimes that all called for capital punishment.
Dialogue: 0,1:00:54.82,1:00:57.82,Default,,0,0,0,,Did the incidence of those crimes diminish?
Dialogue: 0,1:00:57.82,1:00:58.82,Default,,0,0,0,,They did not.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:00.80,1:01:02.80,Default,,0,0,0,,300 crimes were capital.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:02.80,1:01:07.13,Default,,0,0,0,,You look at feudal Europe, you look at the history of Europe.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:07.13,1:01:11.13,Default,,0,0,0,,There were monarchs in which there were hundreds of things for which you get home, etc.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:11.13,1:01:12.13,Default,,0,0,0,,And people went right on doing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:12.13,1:01:14.96,Default,,0,0,0,,They went right on doing it anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:14.96,1:01:16.96,Default,,0,0,0,,Right now, we have three times an outlaw, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:16.96,1:01:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Twice he's been in prison.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:19.94,1:01:22.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Now he goes back.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:22.21,1:01:24.21,Default,,0,0,0,,The apologists say,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:24.21,1:01:26.21,Default,,0,0,0,,you can't put a man in prison for stealing a pizza.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:26.21,1:01:30.51,Default,,0,0,0,,He had one down,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:30.51,1:01:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,two down,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:32.69,1:01:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and he cannot stop stealing a pizza.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:34.69,1:01:37.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Aha.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:37.76,1:01:41.17,Default,,0,0,0,,That shows a mental defect, does it not?
Dialogue: 0,1:01:41.17,1:01:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Faced with horrible torture beyond belief,
Dialogue: 0,1:01:47.90,1:01:50.69,Default,,0,0,0,,traitorism flourished.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:50.69,1:01:56.07,Default,,0,0,0,,In the feudal, in the monarchies of Europe.
Dialogue: 0,1:01:56.07,1:02:00.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Knowing that you're going to be slowly torn to death and boiled in oil,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:00.21,1:02:02.21,Default,,0,0,0,,and gruesome deaths,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:02.21,1:02:04.21,Default,,0,0,0,,people did it anyway.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:07.55,1:02:11.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Who cares who's president?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:11.86,1:02:14.86,Default,,0,0,0,,To get your guy in means you're going to have your tongue torn out,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:14.86,1:02:16.86,Default,,0,0,0,,your eyes poked in, your ears ripped off,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:16.86,1:02:19.86,Default,,0,0,0,,slowly gutted and racked on the rack.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:19.86,1:02:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,People did that all the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:22.59,1:02:25.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:25.01,1:02:26.01,Default,,0,0,0,,All the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:26.01,1:02:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Thousands go to the guillotine, go to the...
Dialogue: 0,1:02:29.42,1:02:30.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:02:30.42,1:02:33.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Because they want to be important and be right,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:33.42,1:02:36.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and in their eyes save the world.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:36.44,1:02:37.44,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:37.44,1:02:39.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Conflict is what the ego likes.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:39.44,1:02:41.44,Default,,0,0,0,,It dislikes peace.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:41.44,1:02:44.44,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see in the Middle East they've had an aversion to peace
Dialogue: 0,1:02:44.44,1:02:46.44,Default,,0,0,0,,for, you know, thousands of years.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:46.44,1:02:49.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And they go into peace frights periodically,
Dialogue: 0,1:02:49.44,1:02:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,but they quickly manage to have a riot and get rid of it.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:52.44,1:02:54.44,Default,,0,0,0,,So, yeah.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:54.44,1:02:58.44,Default,,0,0,0,,Peace would be the end of the reason for their existence.
Dialogue: 0,1:02:58.51,1:03:03.44,Default,,0,0,0,,The raison d'intendre of the fellow that just died there.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:03.44,1:03:06.44,Default,,0,0,0,,He lived off hate and conflict,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:06.44,1:03:08.44,Default,,0,0,0,,and peace was the last thing he wanted.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:08.44,1:03:12.21,Default,,0,0,0,,Blame, conflict, the past.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:12.21,1:03:14.40,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego loves to cling to the past,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:14.40,1:03:17.59,Default,,0,0,0,,and it avoids the present.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:17.59,1:03:19.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It actually clings to fear
Dialogue: 0,1:03:19.59,1:03:24.59,Default,,0,0,0,,based on the idea that it is because of fear that you survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:24.59,1:03:29.71,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't see that merely anticipation and planning is sufficient,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:29.71,1:03:31.71,Default,,0,0,0,,but it hangs on to fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:31.71,1:03:36.73,Default,,0,0,0,,Planning and caution is all that's necessary
Dialogue: 0,1:03:36.73,1:03:38.73,Default,,0,0,0,,to cross the street safely.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:38.73,1:03:41.73,Default,,0,0,0,,You don't have to stand on the curb shaking with fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:41.73,1:03:44.90,Default,,0,0,0,,You anticipate the oncoming, you're anticipating,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:44.90,1:03:47.90,Default,,0,0,0,,so you act from caution rather than fear.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:47.90,1:03:49.90,Default,,0,0,0,,Caution, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:03:50.28,1:03:52.28,Default,,0,0,0,,That's something the ego never thinks about.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:52.28,1:03:56.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It thinks it's either, you know, it's only got this or that.
Dialogue: 0,1:03:56.57,1:03:59.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Ego looks to excuse itself for responsibility,
Dialogue: 0,1:03:59.57,1:04:02.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and it hates being accountable.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:02.88,1:04:06.88,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it likes to deny things rather than admit,
Dialogue: 0,1:04:06.88,1:04:09.88,Default,,0,0,0,,and it's impatient, and it hates to wait.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:09.88,1:04:11.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:11.01,1:04:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,So, those are the characteristics generally.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:14.01,1:04:19.19,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the last one on the attractions and aversions?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:19.19,1:04:20.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:20.30,1:04:26.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Is that the one we just did?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:26.09,1:04:28.09,Default,,0,0,0,,Did we just do this or not?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:28.09,1:04:31.53,Default,,0,0,0,,We did it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:31.53,1:04:32.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't remember doing it.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:37.44,1:04:41.34,Default,,0,0,0,,Everybody who thinks we just did it, raise your hand.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:41.34,1:04:44.63,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay, you win.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:44.63,1:04:50.76,Default,,0,0,0,,I would have sworn we haven't done it yet.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:50.76,1:04:53.05,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:04:53.05,1:04:57.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Which was the next one, Betty?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:57.01,1:04:58.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Hey?
Dialogue: 0,1:04:58.48,1:05:13.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, we're going to look at, no, we want to look at,
Dialogue: 0,1:05:13.42,1:05:17.51,Default,,0,0,0,,well, this is a new slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:17.51,1:05:22.75,Default,,0,0,0,,45 we want.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:22.75,1:05:23.75,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, 45.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:23.75,1:05:24.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We want to look at shame.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:24.75,1:05:26.75,Default,,0,0,0,,We have two slides on shame.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:26.75,1:05:28.42,Default,,0,0,0,,It was too ashamed to show up.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:28.42,1:05:29.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:32.69,1:05:34.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Shame is ashamed of itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:34.69,1:05:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I'm ashamed to be ashamed.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:35.69,1:05:43.61,Default,,0,0,0,,What?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:43.61,1:05:45.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, there's no rush.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:45.76,1:05:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,There's no rush.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:49.42,1:05:53.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Nico's always in a hurry.
Dialogue: 0,1:05:53.98,1:05:56.65,Default,,0,0,0,,We're in no hurry, right?
Dialogue: 0,1:05:56.65,1:06:00.71,Default,,0,0,0,,How often do you get a chance to just sit and do nothing?
Dialogue: 0,1:06:00.71,1:06:02.71,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean, it's a drink.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:02.71,1:06:14.21,Default,,0,0,0,,We've got to hurry up because we've got Nico about 10 after 3.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:14.21,1:06:19.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, about 10 after, so we have about 15 more days.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:19.38,1:06:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, shame seems to have taken a holiday.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:21.38,1:06:25.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I thought we'd start at the bottom.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:25.53,1:06:32.55,Default,,0,0,0,,Shame, because shame often shows up as disgrace, depression, hopelessness,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:32.55,1:06:40.09,Default,,0,0,0,,apathy, sometimes takes clinical forms, not infrequently ends up as suicide,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:40.09,1:06:46.00,Default,,0,0,0,,or the failure to take the necessary steps to survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:46.00,1:06:52.17,Default,,0,0,0,,Shame is banishment.
Dialogue: 0,1:06:52.17,1:06:57.17,Default,,0,0,0,,In primitive society, your life depended on the integrity of the tribe,
Dialogue: 0,1:06:57.17,1:07:03.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the local tribe, and shame, you were banished.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:03.53,1:07:07.53,Default,,0,0,0,,When you were banished from the tribe, you died.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:07.53,1:07:10.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You had no means of survival.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:10.01,1:07:12.01,Default,,0,0,0,,The wild animals got you.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:12.01,1:07:14.01,Default,,0,0,0,,You died of starvation.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:14.01,1:07:18.23,Default,,0,0,0,,So shame was equivalent to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:18.23,1:07:24.48,Default,,0,0,0,,And shame is, at Calibration 20, is very close to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:24.48,1:07:26.48,Default,,0,0,0,,People shrink with shame.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:26.48,1:07:28.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They disappear.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:28.48,1:07:30.48,Default,,0,0,0,,They try to become invisible.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:30.48,1:07:40.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Self-hatred, the giving up of all hope.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:40.76,1:07:42.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Clinically, it requires treatment.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:42.76,1:07:43.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Why?
Dialogue: 0,1:07:43.76,1:07:46.76,Default,,0,0,0,,Because the person in shame is lacking energy
Dialogue: 0,1:07:46.76,1:07:51.76,Default,,0,0,0,,and doesn't even have the energy to avail themself of available energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:51.76,1:07:56.76,Default,,0,0,0,,It can't even take advantage of what is available.
Dialogue: 0,1:07:56.76,1:08:00.30,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, it is the lowest level.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:00.30,1:08:06.01,Default,,0,0,0,,Disgrace, banishment, shame, despair, and hopelessness
Dialogue: 0,1:08:06.01,1:08:13.01,Default,,0,0,0,,are at the bottom of the box.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:13.01,1:08:17.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Not infrequently leads to death.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:17.80,1:08:22.80,Default,,0,0,0,,Clinically, it means, if you see them clinically,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:22.80,1:08:25.85,Default,,0,0,0,,it's a pharmacologic problem.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:25.85,1:08:32.22,Default,,0,0,0,,It also has correlations in brain chemistry, neurochemistry.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:32.22,1:08:36.22,Default,,0,0,0,,The depletion of necessary neurochemicals
Dialogue: 0,1:08:36.22,1:08:41.18,Default,,0,0,0,,allows one to drop to the depths.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:41.18,1:08:42.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:42.27,1:08:45.27,Default,,0,0,0,,The alternative, actually, is death itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:45.27,1:08:49.34,Default,,0,0,0,,And unless someone takes action on the person's behalf,
Dialogue: 0,1:08:49.34,1:08:52.42,Default,,0,0,0,,they will die.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:52.42,1:08:56.15,Default,,0,0,0,,This is a consequence of many things.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:56.15,1:08:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Hmm.
Dialogue: 0,1:08:58.89,1:09:06.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Denial of God is one thing.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:06.36,1:09:10.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmic consequence is another.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:10.57,1:09:12.86,Default,,0,0,0,,Abandonment.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:12.86,1:09:16.38,Default,,0,0,0,,Karmic consequence can be quite severe.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:16.38,1:09:18.38,Default,,0,0,0,,It is also, paradoxically,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:18.38,1:09:21.38,Default,,0,0,0,,the degree to which some people have to hit bottom
Dialogue: 0,1:09:21.38,1:09:23.67,Default,,0,0,0,,with their ego to give up.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:23.67,1:09:28.34,Default,,0,0,0,,It's only when you're clinging to life
Dialogue: 0,1:09:28.34,1:09:30.34,Default,,0,0,0,,by one or two fingers
Dialogue: 0,1:09:30.34,1:09:32.76,Default,,0,0,0,,that you're willing to let go.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:32.76,1:09:35.56,Default,,0,0,0,,The depths of hell.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:35.56,1:09:38.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Hopelessness and despair
Dialogue: 0,1:09:38.65,1:09:41.14,Default,,0,0,0,,beyond description.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:41.14,1:09:44.19,Default,,0,0,0,,And the hopelessness and the despair
Dialogue: 0,1:09:44.19,1:09:47.19,Default,,0,0,0,,and the agony is eternal.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:47.19,1:09:56.22,Default,,0,0,0,,At that level, you get what that means forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:09:56.22,1:09:58.22,Default,,0,0,0,,You are condemned to the dark,
Dialogue: 0,1:09:58.22,1:10:02.26,Default,,0,0,0,,to the blackness, to hopelessness,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:02.26,1:10:06.26,Default,,0,0,0,,without the possibility of any intervention from anywhere.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:09.19,1:10:12.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And time stops.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:12.02,1:10:15.02,Default,,0,0,0,,And just like the top levels of consciousness
Dialogue: 0,1:10:15.02,1:10:18.15,Default,,0,0,0,,are beyond time, you experience eternity.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:18.15,1:10:21.15,Default,,0,0,0,,Anybody who's had a near-death experience knows what that is.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:21.15,1:10:23.57,Default,,0,0,0,,It's outside of time.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:23.57,1:10:28.85,Default,,0,0,0,,At the bottom of the pits is the same timelessness.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:28.85,1:10:32.88,Default,,0,0,0,,The soul is lost and abandoned forever.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:33.88,1:10:38.60,Default,,0,0,0,,As you descend through hell,
Dialogue: 0,1:10:38.60,1:10:41.11,Default,,0,0,0,,the top level is agony.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:41.11,1:10:46.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Suffering, torture, child's play.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:46.27,1:10:48.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Jacks for openers.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:48.27,1:10:51.90,Default,,0,0,0,,What the world considers hell is
Dialogue: 0,1:10:51.90,1:10:54.68,Default,,0,0,0,,just the opening chapter.
Dialogue: 0,1:10:54.68,1:10:58.57,Default,,0,0,0,,Then it gets more severe
Dialogue: 0,1:10:58.57,1:11:01.57,Default,,0,0,0,,and the agony is beyond description.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:01.57,1:11:04.27,Default,,0,0,0,,And then time stops.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:04.27,1:11:06.27,Default,,0,0,0,,As I mentioned before,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:06.27,1:11:09.39,Default,,0,0,0,,as you descend into the pits of hell,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:09.39,1:11:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,you come to a knowingness
Dialogue: 0,1:11:11.39,1:11:14.10,Default,,0,0,0,,which Dante knew.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:14.10,1:11:16.10,Default,,0,0,0,,Abandon all hope, ye who enter here.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:16.10,1:11:18.10,Default,,0,0,0,,There it was, just as plain as day,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:18.10,1:11:20.10,Default,,0,0,0,,as though written on a bulletin board.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:20.10,1:11:24.10,Default,,0,0,0,,How Dante knew it, I don't know.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:24.10,1:11:27.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And from there, it gets bad.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:27.93,1:11:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,And then you experience, like damnation,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:30.93,1:11:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,hopelessness for eternity.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:33.93,1:11:37.85,Default,,0,0,0,,Out of the eternity of hopelessness, then,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:37.85,1:11:40.14,Default,,0,0,0,,out of nowhere,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:40.14,1:11:42.14,Default,,0,0,0,,arose a voice that said,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:42.14,1:11:44.14,Default,,0,0,0,,and if there is a God,
Dialogue: 0,1:11:44.14,1:11:47.17,Default,,0,0,0,,I ask him for help.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:47.17,1:11:50.96,Default,,0,0,0,,And then all of it blacked out.
Dialogue: 0,1:11:50.96,1:11:53.56,Default,,0,0,0,,And the next thing was
Dialogue: 0,1:11:53.56,1:11:57.56,Default,,0,0,0,,standing in the full radiance of divinity
Dialogue: 0,1:11:57.56,1:11:59.56,Default,,0,0,0,,as the allness of creation
Dialogue: 0,1:11:59.56,1:12:01.56,Default,,0,0,0,,and life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:01.56,1:12:11.89,Default,,0,0,0,,If that's what it takes,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:11.89,1:12:16.19,Default,,0,0,0,,then that's what it takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:16.19,1:12:18.48,Default,,0,0,0,,I wouldn't recommend it, but
Dialogue: 0,1:12:18.48,1:12:21.82,Default,,0,0,0,,if that's what it takes,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:21.82,1:12:23.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what it takes.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:23.98,1:12:26.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore, when I see people do serious violations,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:26.98,1:12:28.98,Default,,0,0,0,,serious spiritual violations,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:28.98,1:12:30.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that I know have very bad karmic consequences,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:30.98,1:12:33.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it makes me shudder,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:33.02,1:12:36.27,Default,,0,0,0,,because I know what's coming.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:36.27,1:12:38.27,Default,,0,0,0,,Remember that kid who was executed?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:38.27,1:12:41.72,Default,,0,0,0,,What did he do, blow up a building or something?
Dialogue: 0,1:12:41.72,1:12:43.72,Default,,0,0,0,,And he said, well, I know I'm going to hell,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:43.72,1:12:45.77,Default,,0,0,0,,but there'll be good company there.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:45.77,1:12:47.93,Default,,0,0,0,,When he gets there,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:47.93,1:12:49.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you'll find it isn't that way at all.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:49.93,1:12:51.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It's agony.
Dialogue: 0,1:12:51.93,1:12:53.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So, if that's what it takes,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:53.93,1:12:57.15,Default,,0,0,0,,so some people,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:57.15,1:12:59.15,Default,,0,0,0,,at the bottom of the,
Dialogue: 0,1:12:59.15,1:13:01.47,Default,,0,0,0,,have to go all the way to the bottom,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:01.47,1:13:03.89,Default,,0,0,0,,in order to find God.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:03.89,1:13:06.89,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego's struggle for survival,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:06.89,1:13:08.89,Default,,0,0,0,,at least in this case,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:08.89,1:13:10.89,Default,,0,0,0,,was ferocious.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:10.89,1:13:12.89,Default,,0,0,0,,It was ferocious.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:12.89,1:13:15.92,Default,,0,0,0,,It would not let go.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:15.92,1:13:17.92,Default,,0,0,0,,That's what it took
Dialogue: 0,1:13:17.92,1:13:19.92,Default,,0,0,0,,to make the ego let go.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:19.92,1:13:21.92,Default,,0,0,0,,Usually just slamming it on the fingers will do it,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:21.92,1:13:23.92,Default,,0,0,0,,but no.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:23.92,1:13:27.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, God.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:27.64,1:13:29.64,Default,,0,0,0,,I must have had the ego of a sea urchin
Dialogue: 0,1:13:29.64,1:13:31.64,Default,,0,0,0,,or something on the bottom of the sea.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:31.64,1:13:33.64,Default,,0,0,0,,You know?
Dialogue: 0,1:13:33.64,1:13:35.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All right, so the attractions.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:35.64,1:13:37.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Shame is held into place.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:37.64,1:13:39.64,Default,,0,0,0,,Besides karmic factors,
Dialogue: 0,1:13:39.64,1:13:41.64,Default,,0,0,0,,which in this case was
Dialogue: 0,1:13:41.64,1:13:43.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the karma of having denied
Dialogue: 0,1:13:43.81,1:13:46.81,Default,,0,0,0,,the reality of God in other lifetimes.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:46.81,1:13:48.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Having defied and
Dialogue: 0,1:13:48.81,1:13:51.81,Default,,0,0,0,,perhaps even worse than that.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:51.81,1:13:53.81,Default,,0,0,0,,So that was the undoing of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:53.81,1:13:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,All right.
Dialogue: 0,1:13:56.47,1:13:58.47,Default,,0,0,0,,One thing attractive about shame
Dialogue: 0,1:13:58.47,1:14:00.47,Default,,0,0,0,,is you get to punish yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:00.47,1:14:02.47,Default,,0,0,0,,Therefore,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:02.47,1:14:04.47,Default,,0,0,0,,to forgive yourself would be
Dialogue: 0,1:14:04.47,1:14:07.81,Default,,0,0,0,,just what you won't do.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:07.81,1:14:09.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction is to stay depressed.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:09.81,1:14:11.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The aversion is to choose life.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:11.81,1:14:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,Sometimes it takes
Dialogue: 0,1:14:13.94,1:14:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,electric shock treatments
Dialogue: 0,1:14:15.94,1:14:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,to take the person out of that.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:17.94,1:14:20.81,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction is judgmental
Dialogue: 0,1:14:20.81,1:14:22.81,Default,,0,0,0,,and being judgmental against yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:14:22.81,1:14:24.81,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of surrendering
Dialogue: 0,1:14:24.81,1:14:28.60,Default,,0,0,0,,to God's mercy.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:28.60,1:14:30.60,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction here is to be negative
Dialogue: 0,1:14:30.60,1:14:32.60,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than let go
Dialogue: 0,1:14:32.60,1:14:34.60,Default,,0,0,0,,of your position.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:34.60,1:14:38.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Shame.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:38.36,1:14:40.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You drink, you hide,
Dialogue: 0,1:14:40.36,1:14:42.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't want the light on you
Dialogue: 0,1:14:42.36,1:14:44.36,Default,,0,0,0,,to be visible.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:44.36,1:14:46.36,Default,,0,0,0,,You see yourself as worthless
Dialogue: 0,1:14:46.36,1:14:48.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and your aversion is to affirm
Dialogue: 0,1:14:48.36,1:14:50.36,Default,,0,0,0,,the gift of life itself.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:50.36,1:14:52.36,Default,,0,0,0,,Here your view of self
Dialogue: 0,1:14:52.36,1:14:54.36,Default,,0,0,0,,is unforgiving and rigid
Dialogue: 0,1:14:54.36,1:14:56.36,Default,,0,0,0,,and you don't want to correct it
Dialogue: 0,1:14:56.36,1:14:58.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and be flexible.
Dialogue: 0,1:14:58.77,1:15:00.77,Default,,0,0,0,,So if somebody's stuck in this
Dialogue: 0,1:15:00.77,1:15:02.77,Default,,0,0,0,,and I tell them what Socrates' teaching is,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:02.77,1:15:04.77,Default,,0,0,0,,they'll say, well, that's okay,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:04.77,1:15:06.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but they won't apply it. Huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:06.93,1:15:08.93,Default,,0,0,0,,So they cling to it.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:08.93,1:15:11.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Rather condemn than forgive.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:11.39,1:15:14.00,Default,,0,0,0,,It seeks
Dialogue: 0,1:15:14.00,1:15:16.00,Default,,0,0,0,,mortification
Dialogue: 0,1:15:16.00,1:15:18.00,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than to choose self-worth.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:18.00,1:15:23.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The physicality was
Dialogue: 0,1:15:23.35,1:15:25.35,Default,,0,0,0,,a gift of being a human.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:25.89,1:15:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,What would be the point of mortifying it?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:27.89,1:15:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,But the downside, the Gothic side
Dialogue: 0,1:15:29.89,1:15:31.89,Default,,0,0,0,,of religion at one time
Dialogue: 0,1:15:31.89,1:15:33.89,Default,,0,0,0,,was very into
Dialogue: 0,1:15:33.89,1:15:35.89,Default,,0,0,0,,mortification of the body.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:35.89,1:15:37.89,Default,,0,0,0,,Sackcloth and ashes,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:37.89,1:15:40.47,Default,,0,0,0,,hair shirts, huh?
Dialogue: 0,1:15:40.47,1:15:42.47,Default,,0,0,0,,The attraction here is to denigrate
Dialogue: 0,1:15:42.47,1:15:44.47,Default,,0,0,0,,value and worth
Dialogue: 0,1:15:44.47,1:15:46.47,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than to honor yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:46.47,1:15:49.09,Default,,0,0,0,,All spiritually aligned people
Dialogue: 0,1:15:49.09,1:15:51.18,Default,,0,0,0,,owe it
Dialogue: 0,1:15:51.18,1:15:53.18,Default,,0,0,0,,as an obligation to honor
Dialogue: 0,1:15:53.18,1:15:55.25,Default,,0,0,0,,oneself, to honor
Dialogue: 0,1:15:55.25,1:15:57.60,Default,,0,0,0,,one's dedication.
Dialogue: 0,1:15:57.60,1:15:59.60,Default,,0,0,0,,You owe it to yourself out of honor,
Dialogue: 0,1:15:59.60,1:16:01.81,Default,,0,0,0,,to honor.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:01.81,1:16:03.81,Default,,0,0,0,,Here it would rather denigrate
Dialogue: 0,1:16:03.81,1:16:06.05,Default,,0,0,0,,because then it can indulge
Dialogue: 0,1:16:06.05,1:16:08.59,Default,,0,0,0,,in self-hatred.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:08.59,1:16:10.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego loves hatred.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:10.59,1:16:12.59,Default,,0,0,0,,It loves negativity.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:12.59,1:16:14.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego survives
Dialogue: 0,1:16:14.59,1:16:16.59,Default,,0,0,0,,on the juice it gets out
Dialogue: 0,1:16:16.59,1:16:18.59,Default,,0,0,0,,of its positions.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:18.59,1:16:20.59,Default,,0,0,0,,The ego has no
Dialogue: 0,1:16:20.59,1:16:22.59,Default,,0,0,0,,Kundalini spiritual energy
Dialogue: 0,1:16:22.59,1:16:24.65,Default,,0,0,0,,from which to thrive.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:24.65,1:16:26.65,Default,,0,0,0,,Only animal energy.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:26.65,1:16:28.65,Default,,0,0,0,,So it has to extract, juice
Dialogue: 0,1:16:28.65,1:16:30.65,Default,,0,0,0,,every ego position in order to survive.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:30.65,1:16:35.31,Default,,0,0,0,,The Kundalini
Dialogue: 0,1:16:35.31,1:16:37.31,Default,,0,0,0,,energy is completely different.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:37.31,1:16:39.31,Default,,0,0,0,,All you have to do is say yes
Dialogue: 0,1:16:39.31,1:16:41.31,Default,,0,0,0,,to it and it influences
Dialogue: 0,1:16:41.31,1:16:43.31,Default,,0,0,0,,the field and things come about
Dialogue: 0,1:16:43.31,1:16:45.63,Default,,0,0,0,,effortlessly.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:45.63,1:16:47.63,Default,,0,0,0,,The downside is it loves severity
Dialogue: 0,1:16:47.63,1:16:49.63,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than being benign.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:49.63,1:16:53.26,Default,,0,0,0,,You see the severity,
Dialogue: 0,1:16:53.26,1:16:55.26,Default,,0,0,0,,self-flagellation, suicide
Dialogue: 0,1:16:55.26,1:16:57.46,Default,,0,0,0,,and the
Dialogue: 0,1:16:57.46,1:16:59.46,Default,,0,0,0,,downside of current war.
Dialogue: 0,1:16:59.46,1:17:01.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It's imbalanced and it doesn't want
Dialogue: 0,1:17:01.46,1:17:03.46,Default,,0,0,0,,to see both sides.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:03.46,1:17:05.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It doesn't want to hear the other side of the story.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:05.46,1:17:07.46,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to maintain a distortion.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:07.46,1:17:10.67,Default,,0,0,0,,Next slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:10.67,1:17:22.97,Default,,0,0,0,,That's it for you?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:22.97,1:17:24.97,Default,,0,0,0,,Is this a different slide?
Dialogue: 0,1:17:24.97,1:17:27.68,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh, okay.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:27.68,1:17:29.68,Default,,0,0,0,,It's a different slide.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:29.68,1:17:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you like to blame yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:17:32.02,1:17:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than blame the ignorance of the ego.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:34.02,1:17:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,You refute Socrates' wisdom.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:36.02,1:17:38.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates' wisdom is at
Dialogue: 0,1:17:38.42,1:17:40.42,Default,,0,0,0,,570 and if you're
Dialogue: 0,1:17:40.42,1:17:42.42,Default,,0,0,0,,higher than 570, it's okay to
Dialogue: 0,1:17:42.42,1:17:46.39,Default,,0,0,0,,refute Socrates.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:46.39,1:17:48.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I hate somebody at 170 telling me
Dialogue: 0,1:17:48.39,1:17:50.72,Default,,0,0,0,,Socrates don't know his what from us.
Dialogue: 0,1:17:55.14,1:17:57.14,Default,,0,0,0,,So blame yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:17:57.14,1:17:59.14,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of seeing that
Dialogue: 0,1:17:59.14,1:18:01.35,Default,,0,0,0,,we all make the best
Dialogue: 0,1:18:01.35,1:18:03.35,Default,,0,0,0,,it seemed like the best decision at the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:03.35,1:18:05.35,Default,,0,0,0,,So to blame yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:18:05.35,1:18:07.35,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to stop blaming yourself.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:07.35,1:18:09.35,Default,,0,0,0,,You have to see that the context is different
Dialogue: 0,1:18:09.35,1:18:11.35,Default,,0,0,0,,and the person you are now
Dialogue: 0,1:18:11.35,1:18:13.35,Default,,0,0,0,,is not the same as the person
Dialogue: 0,1:18:13.35,1:18:15.48,Default,,0,0,0,,you were then.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:15.48,1:18:17.48,Default,,0,0,0,,Who you are now is not what you were.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:17.48,1:18:19.68,Default,,0,0,0,,So what you were
Dialogue: 0,1:18:19.68,1:18:21.68,Default,,0,0,0,,was more limited.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:23.89,1:18:25.89,Default,,0,0,0,,So it wants to maintain
Dialogue: 0,1:18:25.89,1:18:27.89,Default,,0,0,0,,its partial selective view
Dialogue: 0,1:18:27.89,1:18:29.89,Default,,0,0,0,,to justify rather than
Dialogue: 0,1:18:29.89,1:18:31.93,Default,,0,0,0,,a balanced.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:31.93,1:18:33.93,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to see the self as loser
Dialogue: 0,1:18:33.93,1:18:35.93,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than
Dialogue: 0,1:18:35.93,1:18:38.53,Default,,0,0,0,,see himself as corrected.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:38.53,1:18:40.53,Default,,0,0,0,,It wants to see life
Dialogue: 0,1:18:40.53,1:18:42.53,Default,,0,0,0,,as the end of the road
Dialogue: 0,1:18:42.53,1:18:45.53,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of the opening to the new.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:45.53,1:18:47.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I'll tell you in the pits of hell
Dialogue: 0,1:18:47.53,1:18:49.53,Default,,0,0,0,,I had no idea that was
Dialogue: 0,1:18:49.53,1:18:51.53,Default,,0,0,0,,the road to the opening of the new.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:55.35,1:18:57.35,Default,,0,0,0,,The opening of the new.
Dialogue: 0,1:18:57.35,1:18:59.35,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you're absolutely
Dialogue: 0,1:18:59.35,1:19:01.52,Default,,0,0,0,,unlovable
Dialogue: 0,1:19:01.52,1:19:03.52,Default,,0,0,0,,and you deny your worth as
Dialogue: 0,1:19:03.52,1:19:05.61,Default,,0,0,0,,a child of God.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:05.61,1:19:07.64,Default,,0,0,0,,All that exists
Dialogue: 0,1:19:07.64,1:19:09.64,Default,,0,0,0,,arises out of one source.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:09.64,1:19:11.64,Default,,0,0,0,,So it's a denial
Dialogue: 0,1:19:11.64,1:19:13.77,Default,,0,0,0,,of the truth of who you are.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:13.77,1:19:15.77,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you see error
Dialogue: 0,1:19:15.77,1:19:18.06,Default,,0,0,0,,as unforgivable.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:18.06,1:19:20.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you see it as a lesson.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:20.06,1:19:22.06,Default,,0,0,0,,Well, lesion is correct too.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:41.39,1:19:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,So all these egos
Dialogue: 0,1:19:43.39,1:19:45.39,Default,,0,0,0,,this is a narcissistic orientation.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:45.39,1:19:47.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's all me.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:47.39,1:19:49.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Oh me, my guilt.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:49.39,1:19:51.39,Default,,0,0,0,,You see how me that is?
Dialogue: 0,1:19:51.39,1:19:53.39,Default,,0,0,0,,It's just me all over the place.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:53.39,1:19:57.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Instead of being concerned for others.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:57.50,1:19:59.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you're serving your personal self.
Dialogue: 0,1:19:59.50,1:20:01.50,Default,,0,0,0,,Here you're going to serve life.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:01.50,1:20:03.50,Default,,0,0,0,,You can see this is an enormous
Dialogue: 0,1:20:03.50,1:20:05.50,Default,,0,0,0,,self-indulgence to wallow
Dialogue: 0,1:20:05.50,1:20:07.50,Default,,0,0,0,,in guilt and shame and penance
Dialogue: 0,1:20:07.50,1:20:09.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and sackcloth and ashes
Dialogue: 0,1:20:09.50,1:20:11.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and drag yourself around as the poor
Dialogue: 0,1:20:11.50,1:20:13.94,Default,,0,0,0,,suffering martyr.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:13.94,1:20:15.94,Default,,0,0,0,,I know people who have tragedies
Dialogue: 0,1:20:15.94,1:20:17.94,Default,,0,0,0,,routine tragedies which everybody has to face
Dialogue: 0,1:20:17.94,1:20:19.94,Default,,0,0,0,,30 years ago
Dialogue: 0,1:20:19.94,1:20:21.94,Default,,0,0,0,,and they're still juicing them.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:21.94,1:20:24.39,Default,,0,0,0,,Still juicing them.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:24.39,1:20:28.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Still juicing them.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:28.02,1:20:30.02,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, because it's self-indulgent
Dialogue: 0,1:20:30.02,1:20:32.02,Default,,0,0,0,,it sees self as
Dialogue: 0,1:20:32.02,1:20:34.02,Default,,0,0,0,,center of life rather than
Dialogue: 0,1:20:34.02,1:20:36.02,Default,,0,0,0,,just a participant.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:36.02,1:20:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,It focuses on oneself
Dialogue: 0,1:20:38.10,1:20:40.10,Default,,0,0,0,,instead of on others.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:40.10,1:20:42.10,Default,,0,0,0,,So you're constantly dumping
Dialogue: 0,1:20:42.10,1:20:44.10,Default,,0,0,0,,your misery of what happened 30 years ago
Dialogue: 0,1:20:44.10,1:20:46.10,Default,,0,0,0,,and trying to milk people
Dialogue: 0,1:20:46.10,1:20:48.44,Default,,0,0,0,,in the present.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:48.44,1:20:50.44,Default,,0,0,0,,And here you've got retrospective falsification
Dialogue: 0,1:20:50.44,1:20:52.44,Default,,0,0,0,,when you say should have
Dialogue: 0,1:20:52.44,1:20:54.47,Default,,0,0,0,,rather than realizing
Dialogue: 0,1:20:54.47,1:20:56.47,Default,,0,0,0,,you were not able to at the time.
Dialogue: 0,1:20:56.47,1:20:58.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I mean you believe
Dialogue: 0,1:20:58.69,1:21:00.69,Default,,0,0,0,,what you thought was true at the time
Dialogue: 0,1:21:00.69,1:21:02.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and you acted to the best.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:02.69,1:21:04.69,Default,,0,0,0,,Whether it turns out to be an error later
Dialogue: 0,1:21:04.69,1:21:06.69,Default,,0,0,0,,is something
Dialogue: 0,1:21:06.69,1:21:08.69,Default,,0,0,0,,different to go on.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:08.69,1:21:10.69,Default,,0,0,0,,So you have to get off the self-indulgence
Dialogue: 0,1:21:10.69,1:21:14.14,Default,,0,0,0,,the attraction.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:14.14,1:21:16.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah, we're going to have Nico next.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:16.93,1:21:18.93,Default,,0,0,0,,Alright, so
Dialogue: 0,1:21:18.93,1:21:20.93,Default,,0,0,0,,that's the first bottom
Dialogue: 0,1:21:20.93,1:21:22.93,Default,,0,0,0,,ego position, shame.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:22.93,1:21:24.93,Default,,0,0,0,,You see it's attraction
Dialogue: 0,1:21:24.93,1:21:26.93,Default,,0,0,0,,with a group like this
Dialogue: 0,1:21:26.93,1:21:28.93,Default,,0,0,0,,it's not where you live
Dialogue: 0,1:21:28.93,1:21:30.93,Default,,0,0,0,,but it's a temporary thing that comes up
Dialogue: 0,1:21:30.93,1:21:32.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you recall something from childhood
Dialogue: 0,1:21:32.93,1:21:34.93,Default,,0,0,0,,some selfishness
Dialogue: 0,1:21:34.93,1:21:36.93,Default,,0,0,0,,you know, you took the last cookie
Dialogue: 0,1:21:36.93,1:21:38.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and your little sister cried
Dialogue: 0,1:21:38.93,1:21:40.93,Default,,0,0,0,,and you're ashamed of that
Dialogue: 0,1:21:40.93,1:21:42.93,Default,,0,0,0,,so it comes up as a fluctuation
Dialogue: 0,1:21:42.93,1:21:45.22,Default,,0,0,0,,but at the time
Dialogue: 0,1:21:45.22,1:21:47.22,Default,,0,0,0,,you're only four years old.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:47.22,1:21:49.42,Default,,0,0,0,,Yeah
Dialogue: 0,1:21:49.42,1:21:51.42,Default,,0,0,0,,and if you didn't get the cookie
Dialogue: 0,1:21:51.42,1:21:53.42,Default,,0,0,0,,you thought your mother didn't love you.
Dialogue: 0,1:21:53.42,1:21:55.46,Default,,0,0,0,,I remember my sister's
Dialogue: 0,1:21:55.46,1:21:57.68,Default,,0,0,0,,birthday, I was like three or something
Dialogue: 0,1:21:57.68,1:21:59.68,Default,,0,0,0,,or four
Dialogue: 0,1:21:59.68,1:22:01.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and I started to cry
Dialogue: 0,1:22:01.68,1:22:03.68,Default,,0,0,0,,my sister's birthday
Dialogue: 0,1:22:03.68,1:22:05.68,Default,,0,0,0,,so I started to cry
Dialogue: 0,1:22:05.68,1:22:07.68,Default,,0,0,0,,and I said, why are you crying
Dialogue: 0,1:22:07.68,1:22:11.11,Default,,0,0,0,,because everybody's bringing her presents
Dialogue: 0,1:22:11.11,1:22:14.43,Default,,0,0,0,,I didn't realize that
Dialogue: 0,1:22:14.43,1:22:16.43,Default,,0,0,0,,had to do with birthday
Dialogue: 0,1:22:16.43,1:22:18.43,Default,,0,0,0,,so she had to explain to me what birthday means
Dialogue: 0,1:22:18.43,1:22:20.50,Default,,0,0,0,,you know what I'm saying
Dialogue: 0,1:22:20.50,1:22:22.50,Default,,0,0,0,,so what you were at the time
Dialogue: 0,1:22:22.50,1:22:24.50,Default,,0,0,0,,at four, I didn't understand
Dialogue: 0,1:22:24.50,1:22:26.50,Default,,0,0,0,,that that's an annual event
Dialogue: 0,1:22:26.50,1:22:28.50,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody was coming to see her
Dialogue: 0,1:22:28.50,1:22:30.50,Default,,0,0,0,,and give her presents and I wasn't getting anything
Dialogue: 0,1:22:30.50,1:22:34.00,Default,,0,0,0,,so when you're looking at your past
Dialogue: 0,1:22:34.00,1:22:36.85,Default,,0,0,0,,just remember
Dialogue: 0,1:22:36.85,1:22:38.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that you were only a three year old
Dialogue: 0,1:22:38.89,1:22:40.89,Default,,0,0,0,,at the time
Dialogue: 0,1:22:40.89,1:22:42.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that was a bad stock to buy
Dialogue: 0,1:22:42.89,1:22:44.89,Default,,0,0,0,,right
Dialogue: 0,1:22:44.89,1:22:46.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so you got real calm
Dialogue: 0,1:22:46.89,1:22:48.89,Default,,0,0,0,,and it became worth 22 cents
Dialogue: 0,1:22:48.89,1:22:50.89,Default,,0,0,0,,well at the time
Dialogue: 0,1:22:50.89,1:22:52.89,Default,,0,0,0,,that's what seemed the right thing to do
Dialogue: 0,1:22:52.89,1:22:54.89,Default,,0,0,0,,so to forgive yourself
Dialogue: 0,1:22:54.89,1:22:56.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you have to
Dialogue: 0,1:22:56.89,1:22:58.89,Default,,0,0,0,,you may have to
Dialogue: 0,1:22:58.89,1:23:00.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you may have to
Dialogue: 0,1:23:00.98,1:23:02.98,Default,,0,0,0,,you may have to
Dialogue: 0,1:23:02.98,1:23:04.98,Default,,0,0,0,,remember in the context of the time
Dialogue: 0,1:23:04.98,1:23:06.98,Default,,0,0,0,,who you are
Dialogue: 0,1:23:06.98,1:23:08.98,Default,,0,0,0,,and what you believe
Dialogue: 0,1:23:08.98,1:23:10.98,Default,,0,0,0,,that's why you acted that way
Dialogue: 0,1:23:10.98,1:23:12.98,Default,,0,0,0,,so it's a falsification now
Dialogue: 0,1:23:12.98,1:23:14.98,Default,,0,0,0,,to reject the past
Dialogue: 0,1:23:14.98,1:23:16.98,Default,,0,0,0,,because the past is not the same
Dialogue: 0,1:23:16.98,1:23:18.98,Default,,0,0,0,,as the present
Dialogue: 0,1:23:18.98,1:23:20.98,Default,,0,0,0,,alright so we're going to break
Dialogue: 0,1:23:20.98,1:23:22.98,Default,,0,0,0,,Nico's going to chant
Dialogue: 0,1:23:22.98,1:23:32.69,Default,,0,0,0,,and after that we're going to have questions and answers
Dialogue: 0,1:23:32.69,1:23:35.69,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to forget my
Dialogue: 0,1:23:35.69,1:23:38.10,Default,,0,0,0,,I don't want to forget that
Dialogue: 0,1:23:38.10,1:23:41.39,Default,,0,0,0,,I have to collapse it
Dialogue: 0,1:23:41.39,1:23:43.39,Default,,0,0,0,,let's see I've got to move these things out of the way
Dialogue: 0,1:23:43.39,1:23:47.11,Default,,0,0,0,,alright
Dialogue: 0,1:23:47.11,1:23:52.06,Default,,0,0,0,,everybody relax
Dialogue: 0,1:23:52.06,1:23:56.05,Default,,0,0,0,,after that
Dialogue: 0,1:23:56.05,1:24:01.22,Default,,0,0,0,,so I would like to
Dialogue: 0,1:24:01.22,1:24:05.55,Default,,0,0,0,,hold in mind
Dialogue: 0,1:24:05.55,1:24:10.85,Default,,0,0,0,,we're going to take a giant leap
Dialogue: 0,1:24:10.85,1:24:13.22,Default,,0,0,0,,and chant the sutra
Dialogue: 0,1:24:13.22,1:24:36.89,Default,,0,0,0,,at this
Dialogue: 0,1:24:36.89,1:24:39.92,Default,,0,0,0,,last moment of your life
Dialogue: 0,1:24:39.92,1:24:43.86,Default,,0,0,0,,and a common moral
Dialogue: 0,1:24:43.86,1:24:45.86,Default,,0,0,0,,since time without beginning
